PSYCHO ( 1960 ) **** Anthony Perkins , Janet Leigh , Vera Miles , John Gavin , Martin Balsam , John McIntire , Simon Oakland . ||| 1
The granddaddy of all slasher films and serial killers , this Alfred Hitchcock classic defined the post-Cold War horror film for generations to come in this rather simple storyline : bank employee Marion Crane ( Leigh ) absconds with a client 's bankroll and winds up the proverbial fly in the spider 's parlor when she winds up in the middle-of- nowhere 's Bates Motel , and mama 's boy Norman Bates ( Perkins in his iconic role ) proving to be more than meets the eye . ||| 1
The perfectly edited shower scene ( the blade never pierces the flesh ! ) ||| 1
by Geroge Tomasini , Bernard Herrmann 's screeching violins score and the all-together ookie finale are American classics in every sense of the word . ||| 1
Best line : `` Mother is n't , what 's the term ? ||| 1
Herself today '' . ||| 1
